<h2 id="overview">Overview:</h2>
<p>The Radon Calculator software was designed in order to calculate the radon concentration in Bq/m3 using Rad Elec E-PERM equipment. The software was developed using Microsoft Visual Basic. Visual Basic is a simple way to create programs for Microsoft Windows that uses ‚ÄúBeginners All-Purpose Symbolic Instruction Code‚Äù programming language. It is easier to create an application or a graphical user interface using the components provided in the software. An executable setup file was generated so that any user can use the ‚ÄúRadon Calculator‚Äù software in his/her computer after installation. The main reasons of making this software are:</p>
<ol>
  <li>The company software is ‚ÄúRadon Report Manager‚Äù and it cost $200. Buying the software wasn‚Äôt necessary as the company already provided us with a manual of how to use the Red Elec equipment and the equations needed to find the concentration of radon. Furthermore, all the equations and the constants were used in ‚ÄúRadon Calculator‚Äù to ease our calculation.</li>
  <li>Inputting the time in ‚ÄúRadon Report Manager‚Äù software takes time as the user needs to repeatedly press the right bottom in order to set the time. For instance, in order to input 32 seconds in the software, an individual need to right click 32 times. This problem was solved in the ‚ÄúRadon Calculator‚Äù software where the user is asked to enter the time manually in 24 hours format.</li>
</ol>

